headline: 3 Dividend Stocks That Are Too Cheap to Ignore and Worth Buying in 2025
summary: Lee Samaha (3M): With a 2.2% dividend yield, 3M isn't quite the dividend stock it used to be.  However, investors won't care too much about that because after years of underperformance, the stock rose by 42% in 2024.
